The paper deals with the computation of flow on terrains, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of imprecise elevations and the consideration of different models for flow computation suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the areas of data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GR). The NP-hardness result for the first model indicates a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) or algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of numerical methods to solve the problem suggests a possible connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
